div.p: WARNING: CRITICAL Without identity mapping, the CPU will page fault on the very next instruction after enabling paging - before your page fault handler can even run! Result: Triple Fault -> System Reset

Virtual Address: 0xC0101234 Bits [31:22] = 0x301 = 768 -> PD Entry 768 Bits [21:12] = 0x001 = 1 -> PT Entry 1
Bits [11:0] = 0x234 -> Page Offset Physical Frame: 0x100000 (kernel) Physical Address: 0x101234

ul.li: Need identity map so code continues after mov cr0, PG=1
Identity map can be removed later
